<exercise checkit-seed="0017" checkit-slug="E1" checkit-title="Linear systems, vector equations, and augmented matrices">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the vector equation.</p>
    <me> x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
-3 \\
-1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
0 \\
1 \\
0 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
4 \\
3 \\
1
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
7 \\
7 \\
2
\end{array}\right] </me>
    <ol>
      <li> Write a system of scalar equations corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
      <li> Write an augmented matrix corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 4 ">
          <mrow>x_{1} &amp; &amp;  &amp;-&amp; 2 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; -4</mrow>
          <mrow>-3 \, x_{1} &amp;+&amp; x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 4 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 7</mrow>
          <mrow>-x_{1} &amp; &amp;  &amp;+&amp; 3 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 7</mrow>
          <mrow> &amp;-&amp; x_{2} &amp;+&amp; x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 2</mrow>
        </md>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 &amp; -4 \\
-3 &amp; 1 &amp; 4 &amp; 7 \\
-1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 &amp; 7 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 2
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

